\subsection{More Qualitative Results}

In this subsection, we provide additional qualitative comparisons to further demonstrate the versatility and robustness of \textbf{InternVL-U} across diverse generation and editing scenarios, including general-purpose synthesis, text-centric rendering, knowledge-informed creation, and reasoning-driven editing. Figures~20--26 present representative examples against strong open-source baselines and selected competitive models.

\paragraph{General image generation.}
As shown in Figure~20, InternVL-U produces visually compelling images with \textbf{high fidelity in fine-grained textures} and \textbf{nuanced lighting effects}. Compared with other open-source models, it better captures subtle material properties (e.g., fabric, metal, skin, and complex surfaces) and adheres more precisely to the user’s instruction intent, resulting in more coherent global structure and more realistic local details.

\paragraph{Text-centric image generation.}
Figure~21 highlights InternVL-U’s strong capability in \textbf{rendering text and symbols}, covering \textbf{Chinese}, \textbf{English}, and \textbf{numerical formulas}. In comparison with unified multimodal open-source models such as \textbf{BAGEL} and \textbf{Ovis-U1}, InternVL-U generates clearer and more accurate glyph shapes with fewer spelling/character errors, while maintaining better visual harmony between text and background. Notably, its performance is \textbf{comparable to Qwen Image} and the large-parameter closed-source commercial model \textbf{Nano Banana Pro}, demonstrating competitive text rendering quality.

\paragraph{Knowledge-informed image generation.}
Figure~22 showcases scenarios where correct rendering requires \textbf{domain/world knowledge}. InternVL-U exhibits superior capability in \textbf{accurate knowledge grounding and visual realization}, effectively integrating relevant knowledge to produce faithful results for complex prompts. Compared with baselines that lack explicit knowledge integration, our model significantly reduces semantic mistakes and improves correctness in visually depicting knowledge-dependent concepts.

\paragraph{General image editing.}
In Figure~23, InternVL-U demonstrates strong general editing performance by producing \textbf{realistic textures and consistent styles} while preserving the \textbf{original image’s lighting, geometry, and structural details}. Across various editing tasks, it better maintains identity and scene consistency, yielding edits that appear natural and well-blended compared to other open-source models.

\paragraph{Text-centric image editing.}
Figure~24 further validates InternVL-U’s capability in \textbf{precise text editing}. The model performs targeted modifications more faithfully, while keeping both \textbf{non-edited text} and \textbf{surrounding visual content} stable. This indicates strong locality control and reduced unintended changes outside the specified region.

\paragraph{Reasoning-informed image editing.}
As shown in Figure~25, InternVL-U outperforms state-of-the-art models on complex editing instructions requiring \textbf{multi-step reasoning} and \textbf{logical constraint satisfaction}. The results illustrate robust execution of diverse constraints, including \textbf{temporal reasoning} (e.g., updating calendar dates), \textbf{spatial and cultural understanding} (e.g., appropriate poem placement), and \textbf{algorithmic rule following} (e.g., correct insertion in a binary search tree). These examples demonstrate that InternVL-U can reliably translate structured reasoning into accurate visual edits.

\paragraph{Special image editing.}
Finally, Figure~26 presents additional special editing cases, further indicating InternVL-U’s broad applicability under challenging or uncommon editing requirements, where both visual realism and instruction adherence are critical.
